a yet allowing urgent need medical treatment depravity situation calls turkey neighbouring states act unilaterally provide safe displaced aleppans meanwhile international community stood position evacuation made neutralise eastern aleppo offering safe passage fighters immediate families leaving arms ability pose threat behind opinion 'palestinisation syrian people ideally would accompanied monitoring mechanism ensure forces assad regime allies respect international law enter east city turn concept evacuation safety full-scale eviction entire community totally unacceptable rebels faced choice accepting rejecting deal true residents eastern aleppo least reported favour remaining homes russia weigh ? video // 5254629219001,0,0,330,186 bcvid_5254629219001 // watch refugees idlib safety major concern 2:19 taking civilians eastern aleppo diminish likelihood eventual return homes evacuation subsequent destruction 2006 nahr el-bared refugee camp lebanon led protracted displacement residents still returning homes decade later given double displacement occurred relatively stable context high international support chances return eastern aleppo vanishingly small worse fate aleppo residents tied destiny communities go similar ethno-sectarian uprooting iranian intervention tie evacuation fate foua kefraya complicated matters existing balance two villages madaya zabadani based gentleman agreement hezbollah jabhat fateh al-sham opinion rubble aleppo isil rises anything shows although russia seems focused mind reaching solution meets objectives finally reached understanding turkey clearly underestimated deviousness deep state iran hides behind excuses control militia ground russians must tread carefully war fought land air inevitably less control situation united nations security council resolution unanimously accepted december 19 establishing monitoring mission welcome development albeit several weeks late russia seek play proactive role monitoring protect civilians uphold reputati