av romanov descendant one nicholas ii nephews member board directors company white russian friends like mad watch celebration russian revolution ? says henderson-stewart memory people suffered revolution business good russia walls central moscow office covered photos famous russians wearing watches prince rostislav romanov right designer board member raketa-petrodvorets watch factory ancestor peter great founded factory 1721 sergey kozmin/al prime minister dmitry medvedev wearing raketa watch putin given raketa watches people n't photo wearing says henderson-stewart proudly despite russian passport settled well country wife also white russian descent french-born children joined moscow years ago reason 'm happy live less agree everything going russia explains generally agree putin internationally russia opinion western criticism russia exaggerated stay away politics total freedom think want says revolution mean russians today ? like ovseenko henderson-stewart many russians struggled impact legacy october revolution regime created centenary russian society seems divided events 100 years ago national survey conducted april independent polling agency levada centre showed 48 percent respondents thought revolution played positive role russian history 31 percent said negative 21 percent could answer question yet 46 percent respondents said bolshevik takeover illegal 49 percent also thought events 1917 caused serious damage russian culture centenary revolution saw public discussions russia burying lenin body destroying mausoleum displayed idea backed chechen president ramazan kadyrov mariya petkova/al jazaeera russian government economical comments revolution putin called tragedy accused lenin responsible disintegration soviet union set nuclear bomb building called russia collapsed need world revolution said speech 2016. according historian nikita sokolov kremlin reluctant talk events 1917 highly problematic current political climate highest cost living europe government re